&lt;p&gt;Greater Manchester Mental Health NHS Foundation Trust (GMMH) seeking to appoint a Service User Research Recruitment Facilitator who will be responsible for supporting the activities of the Research and Innovation team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An excellent opportunity has arisen to become part of the busy Research &amp; Innovation Team. This role has been funded by the Greater Manchester Clinical Research Network to improve and facilitate recruitment of GMMH service users, their families, carers and staff to high quality research studies on the National Institute for Health Research Portfolio.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post-holder will work with researchers and Trust clinical and support services to facilitate timely study set up and effective recruitment to approved research studies utilising new and established systems and processes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post provides an excellent opportunity to gain experience of developing and contributing to service user involvement in research activity. It is essential that the postholder has lived experience of a mental health condition and has experience of using mental health services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The postholder should have substantial administrative experience and experience of working in a research related role would be desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is being offered as a full-time (37.5 hours per week) fixed-term contract until 31st March in the first instance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust is an equal opportunities employer and invites applications from all sections of the community. The position will be based in either our city Centre office or Prestwich base, and remote working may be necessary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameSarah LeoJob titleHead of Research and InnovationEmail addresssarah.leo@gmmh.nhs.ukTelephone number0161 271 0076 or 07342 068 227&lt;/p&gt;
